<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-31T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-31T16:00:00-05:00" n="356" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d356">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 300.115/8720a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Consul General at Hamburg</hi>
                                    (<persName corresp="#p_MHH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-31T16:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 31, 1916, 4 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Endeavor ascertain discreetly and without officially communicating
                                with German authorities whether it is their intention [to] institute
                                prize proceedings in case S. S. <hi rend="italic">Arabic</hi>.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>